						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vālīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga III. Year 32: 1209-10 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records the gift of the villages Vēlūr, Śāttamaṅgalam and Śūralūr ttaḍai, made free of levies by Vīranāraśiṅgadēva <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Yādavarāya for <hi rend="italic">pūjā</hi> and food offerings to the deity Tirukkārikaraippiḷḷaiyār.</p>						

						</summary>
